00:46:17.655 --> 00:46:18.780
DYDINE UMUNYANA: I used to.

00:46:18.780 --> 00:46:19.340
Thank you.

00:46:19.340 --> 00:46:20.500
And I used to.

00:46:20.500 --> 00:46:23.520
Even my mom, I would spend
months not talking to my mom,

00:46:23.520 --> 00:46:27.150
blaming her for not giving
me the life that I want.

00:46:27.150 --> 00:46:29.090
And she doesn't really have any.

00:46:29.090 --> 00:46:31.710
But I will still feel
like I want more from her.

00:46:31.710 --> 00:46:34.230
And whatever that was
not going on in my life,

00:46:34.230 --> 00:46:36.120
I would find somebody to blame.

00:46:36.120 --> 00:46:38.332
The children of perpetrators,
I would blame them

00:46:38.332 --> 00:46:40.290
that they have everything
and I don't, and it's

00:46:40.290 --> 00:46:40.956
because of them.

00:46:40.956 --> 00:46:44.370
So being in a
victimization mode,

00:46:44.370 --> 00:46:47.430
it makes us, like,
giving ourselves

00:46:47.430 --> 00:46:51.880
