00:48:17.800 --> 00:48:21.690
So Rwanda, it's a very
complicated country,

00:48:21.690 --> 00:48:23.250
very complicated.

00:48:23.250 --> 00:48:31.530
And as you can imagine,
after the genocide,

00:48:31.530 --> 00:48:35.550
the country was a
mess, and we had

00:48:35.550 --> 00:48:39.660
a lot of people, different--

00:48:39.660 --> 00:48:42.300
let me see how I'm
going to describe this.

00:48:42.300 --> 00:48:46.055
We had Tutsis who fled
Rwanda, the ones I explained,

00:48:46.055 --> 00:48:47.970
in the 1950s.

00:48:47.970 --> 00:48:50.490
So they grew up in
neighboring countries,

00:48:50.490 --> 00:48:53.730
in Burundi, Congo,
Uganda, and Tanzania.

00:48:53.730 --> 00:48:59.490
And after the genocide,
they say the cause

00:48:59.490 --> 00:49:03.450
of the genocide or the conflict
was because the children who

00:49:03.450 --> 00:49:06.450
were born and grew up in
the neighboring countries,

00:49:06.450 --> 00:49:08.730
they were in exile,
and they were never

00:49:08.730 --> 00:49:12.120
taken as Congolese or Burundian.

00:49:12.120 --> 00:49:14.310
So they were always
refugees there.

00:49:14.310 --> 00:49:16.920
So they always wanted
to come back home.

00:49:16.920 --> 00:49:20.490
And for the Hutu government
that was in power then,

00:49:20.490 --> 00:49:24.610
they told them
that the country--

00:49:24.610 --> 00:49:27.336
Habyarimana, the
president, in his speech,

00:49:27.336 --> 00:49:29.210
he used to-- sometimes
I say, how a president

00:49:29.210 --> 00:49:31.260
can have the kind of speech?

00:49:31.260 --> 00:49:36.600
But he would say that Rwanda
is like a glass full of water.

00:49:36.600 --> 00:49:41.810
And if you try to drop a little
bit of one drop of water in it,

00:49:41.810 --> 00:49:43.640
it spreads.

00:49:43.640 --> 00:49:46.510
So he would say that
Rwanda is full already.

00:49:46.510 --> 00:49:47.380
Nobody can come in.

00:49:47.380 --> 00:49:49.390
If you try to come
in, it will spread.

00:49:49.390 --> 00:49:52.480
And the spread was blood.

00:49:52.480 --> 00:49:55.930
So when the Tutsis
tried to come in 1990,

00:49:55.930 --> 00:49:58.180
they killed a lot of
Tutsis inside the country.

00:49:58.180 --> 00:50:00.760
And even publicly, they
would say on the radios

00:50:00.760 --> 00:50:04.090
that if you try
to come in, we're

00:50:04.090 --> 00:50:08.320
going to kill your families
so that we have space for you.

00:50:08.320 --> 00:50:12.950
So when genocide ended,
after the genocide ended,

00:50:12.950 --> 00:50:17.110
the Tutsis who were living
in the neighboring countries

00:50:17.110 --> 00:50:18.285
came back into Rwanda.

00:50:20.920 --> 00:50:24.970
And the perpetrators fled,
were fleeing to Congo,

00:50:24.970 --> 00:50:29.590
where they still have a rebel
group in Congo that is growing.

00:50:29.590 --> 00:50:32.410
And there were other Hutus
who were going in jail.

00:50:32.410 --> 00:50:34.900
And there were moderate Hutus.

00:50:34.900 --> 00:50:38.530
And there were survivors,
which was 30% of the Tutsis

00:50:38.530 --> 00:50:41.470
in Rwanda, a very small
number of survivors.

00:50:41.470 --> 00:50:43.850
So there were all
these groups coming

00:50:43.850 --> 00:50:46.460
in this little, tiny
country with a difference.

00:50:46.460 --> 00:50:47.920
Some of them are excited.

00:50:47.920 --> 00:50:49.630
Others have lost everything.

00:50:49.630 --> 00:50:53.110
Others are coming back home,
or they have a victory,

00:50:53.110 --> 00:50:55.300
or they are fleeing.

00:50:55.300 --> 00:50:59.710
So it was a very, very
difficult country.

00:50:59.710 --> 00:51:06.240
And just having all those
mixed feelings, it was hard.

00:51:06.240 --> 00:51:08.540
There was not really
a quick solution

00:51:08.540 --> 00:51:11.060
to fix what has just happened.

00:51:11.060 --> 00:51:17.880
The first thing was to bury
the dead bodies and move on.

00:51:17.880 --> 00:51:24.780
So for me as a survivor,
there was no time to grieve.

00:51:24.780 --> 00:51:27.120
There was just no time because
you have to live again,

00:51:27.120 --> 00:51:31.050
and on the same
speed as everyone

00:51:31.050 --> 00:51:34.020
else who was coming home.

00:51:34.020 --> 00:51:38.370
Then the economy
was not as horrible,

00:51:38.370 --> 00:51:41.730
because they came back with
things, although the houses

00:51:41.730 --> 00:51:43.540
were destroyed and all of that.

00:51:43.540 --> 00:51:46.780
But that was for the survivors.

00:51:46.780 --> 00:51:49.017
And we had to go in that
system, go back to school,

00:51:49.017 --> 00:51:50.100
do this and this and this.

00:51:52.850 --> 00:51:54.990
That's why my mom,
now, the trauma's

00:51:54.990 --> 00:51:57.990
coming out now because
she never had that time.

00:51:57.990 --> 00:52:02.070
And now with the
economy and everything--

00:52:02.070 --> 00:52:03.810
before I came, I
worked in rural areas.

00:52:03.810 --> 00:52:08.020
There are places where people
are really, really hungry.

00:52:08.020 --> 00:52:08.680
Really hungry.

00:52:08.680 --> 00:52:11.830
They have one meal a
day, a terrible one.

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:17.260
So of course, that is
happening because also

00:52:17.260 --> 00:52:22.160
