And he was talking to me, kind
of like what you did, kind

00:55:12.015 --> 00:55:15.320
of preparing me for the talk.

00:55:15.320 --> 00:55:17.810
And we were having a
conversation in a car ride.

00:55:17.810 --> 00:55:22.150
And then he was asking me
how I feel when I do this.

00:55:22.150 --> 00:55:23.720
And I said I'm fine.

00:55:23.720 --> 00:55:26.690
But in Rwanda,
culturally, even if you

00:55:26.690 --> 00:55:29.432
asked me, what did you have
for lunch, I wouldn't tell you.

00:55:29.432 --> 00:55:32.390
[LAUGHTER]

00:55:32.390 --> 00:55:34.400
So we always say,
where are you going?

00:55:34.400 --> 00:55:35.785
I'm going down there.

00:55:35.785 --> 00:55:37.080
Or how are you?

00:55:37.080 --> 00:55:40.460
I'm fine, even if I'm dying.

00:55:40.460 --> 00:55:43.020
So he asked me that,
and I said, I'm fine.

00:55:43.020 --> 00:55:46.810
And then he said, you
know, a few years ago, I

00:55:46.810 --> 00:55:49.070
had a friend who was
a Holocaust survivor.

00:55:49.070 --> 00:55:53.630
Her name was Rose [INAUDIBLE].

00:55:53.630 --> 00:55:59.060
And I asked her how she
felt after the talk.

00:55:59.060 --> 00:56:06.260
And then she said, you
know, Dan, when I speak it,

00:56:06.260 --> 00:56:07.570
you hear it.

00:56:07.570 --> 00:56:10.580
And when I speak it, I see it.

00:56:10.580 --> 00:56:13.550
And that really scared me.

00:56:13.550 --> 00:56:15.710
Because I knew that this
is what I wanted to do.

00:56:15.710 --> 00:56:17.780
And I know a lot of
survivors don't do it.

00:56:17.780 --> 00:56:21.770
But then I knew that it takes me
a long time to get over a talk.

00:56:21.770 --> 00:56:23.480
It takes me at least--

00:56:23.480 --> 00:56:26.870
I have to be able to call my
friends right after the talk.

00:56:26.870 --> 00:56:28.220
I have to distract myself.

00:56:28.220 --> 00:56:30.770
It takes me at least a
few days or two weeks

00:56:30.770 --> 00:56:32.900
to really get over the talk.

00:56:32.900 --> 00:56:36.140
And I thought the more I
do it, I would get better.

00:56:36.140 --> 00:56:37.550
So I asked him how old was she.

00:56:37.550 --> 00:56:40.090
And he said she was 91.

00:56:40.090 --> 00:56:42.096
[LAUGHS]

00:56:42.096 --> 00:56:44.440
And I was like,
that's not promising.

00:56:44.440 --> 00:56:48.170
How am I going to live my
70-something years doing that

00:56:48.170 --> 00:56:48.710
to myself?

00:56:48.710 --> 00:56:50.223
Maybe I should quit.

00:56:50.223 --> 00:56:54.445
But when he was saying it
I said, oh, that's not fun.

00:56:54.445 --> 00:56:56.320
I don't know if I'm
going to keep doing this.

00:56:56.320 --> 00:56:58.220
And he said, but
Dydine, remember, she

00:56:58.220 --> 00:57:01.460
started when she was 81.

00:57:01.460 --> 00:57:05.150
So she really never talked
about it until she was 81,

00:57:05.150 --> 00:57:08.810
and it was all inside her.

00:57:08.810 --> 00:57:13.610
And I said, oh, maybe
because I started young,

00:57:13.610 --> 00:57:15.332
maybe at 40 I'll be fine.

00:57:15.332 --> 00:57:16.940
[LAUGHTER]

00:57:16.940 --> 00:57:18.280
So I want to keep doing it.

00:57:18.280 --> 00:57:20.090
I know sometimes it's hard.

00:57:20.090 --> 00:57:23.210
When I met Aaron, when
I published the book,

00:57:23.210 --> 00:57:25.000
I was quitting public speaking.

00:57:25.000 --> 00:57:27.490
I said, I should just go work
somewhere in entertainment.

00:57:27.490 --> 00:57:30.924
And I went to CBS and
"Entertainment Tonight."

00:57:30.924 --> 00:57:32.840
And Aaron was like,
Dydine, when you're ready,

00:57:32.840 --> 00:57:35.600
just let me know
because you have to be

00:57:35.600 --> 00:57:37.440
out there inspiring people.

00:57:37.440 --> 00:57:42.424
And by that time, I would
be sobbing on the stage.

00:57:42.424 --> 00:57:44.090
Of course, I did cry
a little bit today,

00:57:44.090 --> 00:57:48.160
but I used to really,
really cry, like sob.

00:57:48.160 --> 00:57:50.240
And I was like,
this is not pretty.

00:57:50.240 --> 00:57:52.440
I should just not do this.

00:57:52.440 --> 00:57:57.470
So the more I do it, the
more I remember most of them.

00:57:57.470 --> 00:58:00.210
Because the more I think
about it, it comes back.

00:58:00.210 --> 00:58:01.910
But I think--

00:58:01.910 --> 00:58:04.100
I take meditation classes now.

00:58:04.100 --> 00:58:07.340
And my meditation
teacher told me, what

00:58:07.340 --> 00:58:09.800
happens to you happens for you.

00:58:09.800 --> 00:58:12.410
So it really maybe
happened for me

00:58:12.410 --> 00:58:14.340
so that I can help someone else.

00:58:14.340 --> 00:58:18.210
So I want to do this
for the rest of my life.

00:58:18.210 --> 00:58:21.770
And hopefully, at
40 or 30-something,

00:58:21.770 --> 00:58:25.620
I won't be still seeing it.

